S'The Kindle app puts over a million books at your fingertips.  It\xe2\x80\x99s the app for every reader, whether you\xe2\x80\x99re a book reader, magazine reader, or newspaper reader\xe2\x80\x94and you don\xe2\x80\x99t need to own a Kindle to use it.  Choose from over a million Kindle books from the Kindle Store or enjoy popular magazines like The Economist and Reader\xe2\x80\x99s Digest with high-resolution color images.*\xe2\x80\xa2 Read Free Books\xe2\x80\x94Choose from thousands of free ebooks such as Pride & Prejudice or The Adventures of Sherlock Holmes.\xe2\x80\xa2 Shop for Books\xe2\x80\x94Easily shop for ebooks, including new releases and New York Times Best Sellers.\xe2\x80\xa2 Use the Built-In Dictionary, Google, and Wikipedia\xe2\x80\x94The Kindle app has a built-in dictionary that allows you to look up words instantly while you\xe2\x80\x99re reading your ebooks.  Simply tap and hold a word to view its definition or use the Google and Wikipedia links to get more information.\xe2\x80\xa2 Sync Your eBooks\xe2\x80\x94The Kindle app lets you read the same book across devices and automatically syncs where you left off so you can start reading on one device and pick up where you left off on another device.  The app syncs your furthest page read, bookmarks, notes, and highlights between Android, PC, Mac, iPad, iPhone, iPod touch, BlackBerry, Windows Phone 8, and any of our Kindle devices using our Whispersync technology. \xe2\x80\xa2 Sample Books Before You Buy\xe2\x80\x94Read the first chapter of a book for free before you decide to buy.\xe2\x80\xa2 Customize Your Reading\xe2\x80\x94Choose your preferred font size, screen brightness, background color, and orientation (portrait or landscape) to read your books.\xe2\x80\xa2 Borrow eBooks from the Library\xe2\x80\x94Check out ebooks from your local library and have them delivered wirelessly to your Kindle app.\xe2\x80\xa2 Read print replica textbooks on Android tablets.  Print Replica Kindle books maintain the rich formatting and layout of their related print editions and provide features to help students study smarter including ability to highlight passages, add margin notes, and search for keywords.  Whispersync technology saves and synchronizes your bookmarks, notes, and highlights across your devices.* Selection for U.S. users only; selection and price of ebooks and e-periodicals vary by country.Recent changes:4.0.2\xe2\x80\xa2 Fixed a bug with notes, dictionary, and highlights not displaying.\xe2\x80\xa2 Fixed a bug for missing table of contents.Tip: Book options are available by tapping the page and then the \xe2\x80\x9cAa\xe2\x80\x9d icon.4.0.0\xe2\x80\xa2 Redesigned library experience.\xe2\x80\xa2 Carousel displays recent items on the Kindle home screen.\xe2\x80\xa2 Navigation panel organizes content for quick access.\xe2\x80\xa2 Browse all your items in the Cloud or just the downloads on your device.\xe2\x80\xa2 Explore and download popular samples in the Kindle Store.'
